		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Factions - How To Raise Em<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Sep 25th 2:46 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=100144357918952&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=100144357918952&post=1&replyto=100144357918952"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=100144357918952></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=803"><span id=Scholar>GiddyGonzalus</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>155 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=GiddyGonzalus&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Pally's need faction hits like you wouldn't believe for many of their quests. Here's a few tips on how to raise them:<br><br>Qeynos Paladins:<br>Turn in Bandit Sashes (from Bandits in the Karanas)- good faction and decent money<br>Turn in Bone Chips - this is a decent way to PL up to level 7 if u want, just get the box from the Pally in Qeynos and combine 6 Bone Chips. The xp is faster then turning in 4 Bone Chips to the Cleric.<br><br>Felwithe Paladins:<br>Turn in those Bone Chips to the Cleric Guild, 4 at a time.<br><br>Kaladim Paladins:<br>Turn in Bone Chips to the Paladin Guild.<br><br>Freeport Paladins:<br>Tumpy Tonics - This is a GREAT way of increasing faction with the FP Paladins, the Coalition of Tradefolk, and the Coalition of Tradefolk Illegal. Fill yourself up with backpacks and take only 1 stack of food and about 60 water, hop on the boat to Ocean of Tears and get off on Sister Isle, run to the merchant there and fill up on Kiola Nuts, then hop back on the boat (if your fast you can catch the same boat) and get off in Butcherblock. Run to Kaladim and give Tumpy (or Trumpy - the booze merchant near the Arena) 1 kiola nut and 1 water. He gives u a Tumpy Tonic, do this till you're out of nuts. Hop back on the boat to FP and wait in the Seafairer's Roost (by the dock) for Groflah (he spawns at night). Hand him the tonics (you can give him 4 stacks of 4 tonics at a time). BINGO! You're faction goes up. With 200 Tonics (I could have used less) I increased my Ogre Warrior from KoS to the Paladins to Allied.<br><br>Erudine Paladins:<br>There's got to be a better way than this, but the only way I know is to keep killing the fellow that spawns at the dock in Tox Forrest.<br><br>Freeport Clerics:<br>This is the worst faction to have to raise. There's 2 ways:<br>1) Kill the piranha in NFP and hand them in to the Cleric Guild using the pouch they give you. Spawn rate is sssslllloooowwww and it's funner watching the grass grow in winter time.<br>2) Kill FP Militia and hand in their helmets. This works well, but it does make you KoS in East and West FP.<br><br>Felwithe Clerics, Kaladim Clerics, Qeynos Clerics:<br>Bone Chips, Bone Chips, Bone Chips<br><br>Qeynos Warrios:<br>Hunt Gnolls in Blackburrow, hand in their fangs to the Warrior Guild, take the item he gives you and turn them in to the merchant in the back of the shop where Tumpy spawns (near the Qeynos South Docks), then sell or drink the Blackburrow Stout he gives you. Beware that this does decrease your faction with the Corrupt Qeynos Guards so keep conning them to make sure you don't go KoS.<br><br>BONE CHIPS:<br>Though Bone Chips are available all across Norrath, no place is more bountiful than Everfrost. Not only are there hordes of decaying skeletons, but Barbarians have no class use for them so Bone Chips are frequently available at the merchants as well.<br><br>Well, hope this helps those that are starting out. I hope that the veterans out there will post any corrections and additions to my info. Happy Hunting!<br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>________<br><br>I've travelled this world and have seen many wondrous things. You are not one of them.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
